The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, April 02, 2004 				 Power Finance net up 37% to Rs 1600 crore 
																								New Delhi, April 1 (PTI): Power Finance Corporation (PFC) today announced a 37 per cent jump in net profit to Rs 1,601 crore for fiscal 2003-04 largely due to adoption of new accounting norms without which profits would have been lower by Rs 300 crore.																								PFCs net profit rose Rs 429 crore during the year from Rs 1,172 crore in the previous fiscal, chairman and managing director A. A. Khan said today. 																								However, profits would have been lower by Rs 300 crore at Rs 1,300 crore in the absence of the new methodology, he added. The corporation had switched to calculating income on accrual basis from cash basis since April 2003.																								Profits also rose owing to increase in income by 20 per cent.																								Khan said disbursements climbed 22 per cent during the period to Rs 8,974 crore, up from Rs 7,338 crore in the year-ago period. Sanctions went up 17.8 per cent to Rs 16,472 crore compared with Rs 14,001 crore year-on-year, while recovery rate remained flat at 99 per cent. 
